OL,3,CSupporters see fresh chance to revive
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FSupporters of assisted dying believe
OL,7,Fthey may have been handed a second
OL,8,Fchance to pass the bill, which ran out
OL,9,Fof time in the House of Lords.
OL,11,FA random draw of names in what is
OL,12,Fknown as the 'private members ballot'
OL,13,Fhas given several supportive MPs the
OL,14,Fopportunity to bring the bill back.
OL,16,FAmong the top five MPs drawn, three
OL,17,Fpreviously voted for the assisted
OL,18,Fdying bill.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
