OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1779379877
OL,3,CSupporters see fresh chance to revive
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FIn February, as the bill looked to be
OL,7,Fstalling, Andrew George laid a motion
OL,8,Fin the Commons stating that "the use
OL,9,Fof filibuster tactics in the House of
OL,10,FLords to frustrate the majority will
OL,11,Fof the democratically elected House of
OL,12,FCommons is unacceptable".
OL,14,FSupporters want to copy across the
OL,15,Fdetails of Kim Leadbeater's Terminally
OL,16,FIll Adults (End of Life) Bill and try
OL,17,Fto pass it again.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31004
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1779379877
OL,3,CSupporters see fresh chance to revive
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FIf necessary, they want to use the
OL,7,FParliament Act, which can allow a bill
OL,8,Fto be forced through the House of
OL,9,FLords if peers try to block it twice.
OL,11,FHowever, supporters believe that they
OL,12,Fneed the help of an MP drawn in the
OL,13,Ftop three names to have the best
OL,14,Fchance of reviving the bill.
OL,16,FThe higher an MP is drawn, the sooner
OL,17,Ftheir bill can be introduced to
OL,18,Fparliament, giving it more time to
OL,19,Fpass.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
