PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1779379877
OL,3,CSupporters see fresh chance to revive
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FThe first name drawn, Conservative MP
OL,7,FSir Desmond Swayne, opposed the
OL,8,Fassisted dying bill.
OL,10,FBut the second name, Labour's Lauren
OL,11,FEdwards, has been strongly supportive.
OL,13,FAfter voting for assisted dying last
OL,14,Fyear, she said: "I believe this Bill
OL,15,Fis one of the most important,
OL,16,Fcompassionate, and empowering changes
OL,17,Fto healthcare we've seen in a
OL,18,Fgeneration."
OL,26,@vD@QOUzD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
