OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1779379877
OL,3,CSupporters see fresh chance to revive
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FShe told The Guardian: "A lot of
OL,12,Famendments were rejected that I think
OL,13,Fcould have made it a lot stronger."
OL,15,FEven if an MP supports the bill, they
OL,16,Fwould need to consider whether they
OL,17,Fwanted to tackle what has become a
OL,18,Fdivisive (and sadly, at times,
OL,19,Fvicious) debate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
