OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1779379877
OL,3,CSupporters see fresh chance to revive
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FSupporters and opponents of the bill
OL,7,Fcomplained of abuse and even death
OL,8,Fthreats during the last debate.
OL,10,FOn the one hand, bringing the bill
OL,11,Fback would raise an MP's profile,
OL,12,Fpossibly even securing them a place in
OL,13,Fthe history books (for better or
OL,14,Fworse, depending on your viewpoint).
OL,16,FBut on the other hand, they'd be
OL,17,Fthrowing themselves into the lion's
OL,18,Fden.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
